<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 25 at 8:07AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Fog Affecting Portions of Deep South Texas...
Surface observations and visible satellite continue to show patchy
dense fog occurring across Zapata, Hidalgo, and Starr Counties
this morning. Prevailing visibilities will range from 1 to 3
miles in the fog, with some patchy dense fog reducing the
visibility to one half of a mile or less in some areas. Fog should
lift and dissipate by 9 or 9:30 AM.
Motorists are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and
avoid following other vehicles too closely in the areas of denser
fog through the evening and overnight hours.</description>
